And after Bosnia and Herzegovina declared its independence from Yugoslavia, the dissenting Bosnia Serb forces immediately encircled the capital city of Sarajevo, occupying the surrounding mountains and trapping the residents inside the city walls in hopes of crippling this newly independent government.

