This is way easier said than done.

25:52.543 --> 25:56.848
There is a real cost to living in this way.

25:56.888 --> 26:01.453
The people in Thessalonica thought that they were crazy for living like this.

26:01.714 --> 26:06.099
It literally says in verse eight that they were disturbed when they heard these things.

26:07.761 --> 26:15.890
See, they thought that these people were fools for placing their hope in a crucified king rather than a living emperor.

26:16.642 --> 26:19.965
And we see this class played out in verse nine when the authorities couldn't find Paul.

26:20.005 --> 26:22.568
They didn't just let Jason go with a warning.

26:22.588 --> 26:25.390
It says that they took money as security from him.

26:26.712 --> 26:30.455
In the original language and context, this was a massive legal bond.

26:30.595 --> 26:35.200
Jason literally had to put his bank account on the line for the sake of the kingdom.

26:37.021 --> 26:46.130
You see, following Jesus wasn't just an intellectual exercise or a spectator sport for Jason, but rather it meant practicing a different way of life.

26:47.330 --> 26:57.964
And we see here that his wallet followed his worship.

26:57.984 --> 27:01.529
There is a real cost to living counter-culturally for Jesus.

27:01.589 --> 27:04.493
And the reality is not everyone will understand.

27:06.135 --> 27:07.517
Some people will call it crazy.

27:09.260 --> 27:10.722
Some people will even call it foolish.

27:12.504 --> 27:17.010
But as Paul reminds us in 1 Corinthians 1, the foolishness of God is wiser than men.

27:17.730 --> 27:20.253
and the weakness of God is stronger than men.

27:21.414 --> 27:27.482
Because the thing is what looks crazy in an upside down world is actually the highest form of sanity.

27:30.966 --> 27:38.815
So as we close this morning, I want to go back to Vidran Smayalovich, the cellist of Sarajevo.

27:42.199 --> 27:44.882
You see, when Smayalovich sat in that cratered bakery,

27:46.050 --> 27:51.255
I don't think he was under any illusion that his cello would be able to stop mortar shells from falling.

27:53.397 --> 27:57.541
See, he knew he was outnumbered, outgunned, outmanned.

28:01.525 --> 28:05.208
But he also knew that their world wasn't the way that it was supposed to be.

28:07.250 --> 28:11.394
He knew that living under the tyranny of death and destruction wasn't how they were meant to live.

28:11.454 --> 28:15.218
And so he sat and he played a different song.

28:18.114 --> 28:22.361
He played an alternate tune that lifted the eyes of the people to an alternate world.

28:23.663 --> 28:26.508
A world where beauty would rise out of brokenness.

28:27.750 --> 28:32.397
A world where oppression and injustice, injustice would not have the final word.

28:34.641 --> 28:45.458
And again, that's my prayer for us as a church, that in the power of the Holy Spirit, we would be able to enter into these contentious spaces and that we would play the music of the gospel.

28:48.354 --> 28:53.241
Because listen, we live in a city that's under its own kind of siege.

28:55.084 --> 28:59.671
It's the siege of anxiety that enslaves us to fear and blinds us to hope.

29:01.213 --> 29:05.419
It's the siege of hustle culture that tells us that we're only the sum of what we can produce.

29:07.582 --> 29:11.388
It's the siege of political tribalism that tells us to hate our neighbors.

29:13.531 --> 29:18.258
It's the siege of comparison that tells us that we're only as valuable as our highlight reel.

29:18.786 --> 29:22.051
or our next big break, or our proximity to power.

29:23.533 --> 29:28.140
You see the decrees of our culture are constantly trying to pull us into the rubble.

29:30.784 --> 29:34.930
The church, we serve a different King.

29:36.672 --> 29:41.740
And as witnesses of Jesus, we are called to be like the cellists of Los Angeles.

29:42.801 --> 29:45.906
We're called to walk into the ruins of our workplaces,

29:46.498 --> 29:54.429
Our broken family dynamics, our divided neighborhoods, not with a weapon to crush or an argument to win, but with a song to play.

29:56.732 --> 30:02.800
Because when we preach a different king, we tell the world that it's the cross and not a sword.

30:03.642 --> 30:04.623
That's the power of God.

30:06.145 --> 30:11.853
When we participate in a different kingdom, we prove that a new family is possible across every divide.

30:13.795 --> 30:15.698
And when we practice a different way of life,

30:16.898 --> 30:23.367
We show our city that following the teaching and ways of Jesus is the pathway to true life and flourishing.

30:26.292 --> 30:33.582
So like Paul and Silas, may we be a people who stand guilty as charged.

30:33.602 --> 30:44.498
May we be a people who are so devoted to our king, so rooted in his kingdom and so faithful in our practices that the world would look at reality L.A. and say, look,

30:44.994 --> 30:49.138
Those who have turned the world upside down have come here also.

30:51.060 --> 30:59.168
And as we continue to play the music of the gospel, we can look forward to the day when an upside-down world is turned right-side up.

30:59.808 --> 31:00.109
Amen?

31:01.150 --> 31:01.610
Let's pray.

31:03.132 --> 31:14.002
God, we thank you for the Thessalonians church that even in the midst of much hostility and affliction we read in the gospel, we read in the books that

31:14.754 --> 31:22.162
The Gospel took root and that these early sisters and brothers of ours would go on to be a launching pad for missions in the ancient world.

31:24.405 --> 31:32.875
And so I pray this morning that we would follow their lead, pledging ourselves to a different king and patterning our lives after a different kingdom.

31:35.237 --> 31:42.706
And in a city that creates and exports narratives, may we be a people who are faithful to tell the greatest story ever told.

31:44.866 --> 31:56.427
And as we proclaim the gospel in word and indeed, we pray that you would renew Los Angeles and that you would receive all of the glory, all of the honor and all the praise that are do your name.

31:58.170 --> 32:00.334
We pray this in the beautiful name of Jesus.

32:01.376 --> 32:03.320
Amen.

32:03.340 --> 32:04.201
Thank you for listening.

32:04.762 --> 32:09.010
For more audio and video content, please visit realityla.com.

